        public UniversalServeRequest<?> toBinary()
                                  throws Flow.FlowOperationException
        Description copied from interface: ServeRequest
        Returns a request whose isEmpty(), isBinary() or isFile() method will return true and getBinary() or getFile() will return a binary non-null representation of a response. When a response is already meets conditions specified this method should return exactly the SAME response object. The "Character-Encoding" of "Content-Type" attributes of a current response and "Accept-Charset" or "Accept-Type" attributes of current query should be considered when possible. "UTF-8" encoding should be used by default.
